text.section:
A person, with the intent to unlawfully extort money, property, labor, services, or anything of value from another, may not verbally threaten to:
accuse any person of a crime or of anything that, if true, would bring the person into contempt or disrepute; or
cause physical injury to a person;
inflict emotional distress on a person;
cause economic damage to a person; or
cause damage to the property of a person.
